view-if: ccp_relation < 70 and not london_fm == "Hume"
unavailable-subtitle: [? if ccp_relation <= 60 : Our relations are not good enough. ?] [? if resources < 1 : We do not have enough resources. ?] [? if not ccp_london: We do not have the necessary influence. ?]
subtitle: -1 resource. Percy is likely to be friendlier to us than Kaas.
on-arrival: resources -= 1; ccp_leader = "Percy"; ccp_ideology = "Liberal"; white_collar_ccp -= 3; white_collar_cup += 2; white_collar_other += 2; white_collar_lab += 1; urban_workers_ccp += 2; other_workers_ccp += 8; ccp_relation += 4; ccp_disintegration += 1; lib_left += 2; cnlp_left += 1; cnlp_cohesion += 1;
face-image: img-lab/portraits-lab/PercyEustace.jpg

#possibly something about liberal-ccp collaboration

With our connections, especially with the London branch of the party, as well as a professional campaign, we have been able to influence the <span style="color: #1375d6;">**CCP**</span> delegates to support Eustace Percy as the new <span style="color: #1375d6;">**CCP**</span> leader. He has long been a friend of the <span style="color: #e31414;">**Labour**</span> party, and will be more inclined to collaborate with us compared to Rennell. He also increases the appeal of the <span style="color: #1375d6;">**CCP**</span> to the working class, though it comes at the cost of white-collar support.

@hume
choose-if: london_fm == "Hume"
unavailable-subtitle: Hume lacks the influence necessary to have a real chance.
on-arrival: ccp_leader = "Hume"; ccp_ideology = "Moderate Conservative"; hume_path = 1; ccp_relation -= 8; ccp_disintegration += 2; white_collar_ccp += 8; upper_ccp += 5; farmers_ccp -= 15; farmers_cup += 10; urban_workers_ccp += 5; other_workers_ccp -= 5; unemployed_ccp += 3; farmers_lab += 5; other_workers_lab += 5; white_collar_other += 4; farmers_other += 2 if cup_ideology != "Moderate"; farmers_lib += 4; farmers_cnlp += 2; upper_lib -= 4; lib_right += 1; cnlp_left += 1; cnlp_cohesion += 1; liberal_cooperation += 1; bourgeois_cooperation += 1; white_collar_cup -= 2 if cup_ideology == "Radical"; upper_cup -= 3 if cup_ideology == "Radical"; farmers_cup += 3 if cup_ideology != "Radical"; london_fm = "Ray";
face-image: img-lab/portraits-lab/HumeGeorge.jpg

George Hume has been elected as the chairman of the <span style="color: #1375d6;">**CCP**</span>. He seems to represent a rightward turn from Hogg, despite his reformist background, and will preside over a <span style="color: #1375d6;">**CCP**</span> less inclined to compromise with the left. He views the <span style="color: #1375d6;">**CCP**</span> as a predecessor to a <span style="color: #1375d6;">united</span> <span style="color: #002c6e;">right</span>-<span style="color: #ffbb00;">wing</span> <span style="color: #ffd600;">party</span>, and will work to bring together <span style="color: #002c6e;">reactionaries</span>, <span style="color: #1375d6;">conservatives</span>, and <span style="color: #ffbb00;">liberals</span>, preferably to govern without the  <span style="color: #e31414;">**Labour**</span> party.

The <span style="color: #1375d6;">**CCP**</span>'s farmer wing is in uproar over the vote, despite Hume conceding his leadership of the House delegation and the First-Ministership to his allies in Sam Hoare and William Ray, respectively. [? if cup_ideology == "Radical": His election also attracts some middle-class and industrialist members of the  <span class="tooltip-text" title="Conservative & Unionist Party" style="color: #002c6e;">**CUP**</span>, who may result in a shift of the party towards the right. ?]
